                "invention-title": "Solar-hydrogen energy system"
            },
            "abstract": {
                "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of solar energy, wind energy, hydrogen energy and the like. Due to the characteristics of intermittence and not easy storage and transportation of renewable energy resources, such as solar energy, wind energy, and the like, a high-efficient and clean energy carrier is required to be the bridge between the renewable energy resources and users, and hydrogen is known to be the most potential energy carrier in future owning to the characteristics of cleanliness and high-efficiency. The new technology of water electrolysis can recover the electric quantity consumed by electrolysis and reuses the recovered electric quantity to produce hydrogen by utilizing a systematic recovery theory, thereby solving the bottleneck problem of large power consumption for water electrolysis and leading the low-cost industrialization of a solar-hydrogen energy system to be possible."
